rComments: He actually expects people to APPLY knowledge, not just regurgitate.  Prof. Fullard's tests were very challenging, but fair. I wasn't a great student, but I worked hard and did really well in his classes. The people failing were the ones not coming to class, not doing the reading, and not taking time to figure it out. Get ready for the real-world!

Had him for BIO204 and still with him for 304. He's an amazing lecturer, keeps you interested and although the concepts are difficult, he explains it in such clarity it seems a lot easier. NIA2 is amazing and you're bound to get at least 75-80 in each tutorial assignment. Tests are brutal though, he kills the entire class on them.
He keeps you interested in the material. His slides are helpful. DEFINITELY must go to the classes, loads of info to retain but he's a great prof :D
For some, tests may be difficult if they find reading hard. This isn't high school, don't expect to be spoon fed.
Seams like he is full of himself. Talks way to fast, and his tests are brutal. He does have enthusiasm to his material but his expectations are beyond high they are rediculous

Prof Fullard always made me laugh in class, most of the time because he dresses like a pirate in tight black jeans and a loose white top with black boots. I always understand what he says in class but the tests are incomprehensible. Really tough class. I recommend staying for the tutorials, they're helpful in completing the assignment!

This guy is horrible. One of the worst professors on campus (next to Shin and Anderson). Very enthusiastic... but is a major prick. On a quiz covering ten pages, the class average was 47%! He also thinks he is special for some reason.

When I went to him for advice on doing better in his class after a rough 2months (due to a death in the family), he was rude and insensitive and didn't listen to word I said. I left his office in tears. Will NEVER again take a class he teaches. I even made a formal written complaint to the Bio department. But will say he's a decent lecturer.
worse class by far!! don't take it if you don't have to. some advice, if you're late by 1min to hand in your assign, you'll get a 0 on that assign.!!!
...wild course, places I never thought of going.  This guy rocks and rocks!

Very hard course with a LOT of work to be handed in.  He moves too fast through lectures, but shows great enthusiasm.  Seems a bit mean when you approach him personally and his tests are hard and done during extreme time constraints!
Hard prof.  He explains everything well, but his tests are killer.
...major hottie, whole lotta burnin' luv, I'd take him home to meet my mom if I trusted her with him!!!
Hes full of himself...Talks too damn fast
He tests u from**** he didnt even assign...nuts

Really good course. Prof is amazing at explaining concepts. Recommend this course but the labs are a bit long and pretty tedious and difficult. I would take this course again if I had a choice to do so.
asks Qs from sections of the text not assigned, but reccommended...is a prick
